 are older than traditionally assumed.\nSimilarly, although stars which power Herbig-Haro flows appear to have larger\nmass outflow rates, their stellar and circumstellar properties are generally\nindistinguishable from those of stars that do not power these flows.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Aug 2004 21:39:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-07-18"}
